      String username = "root", password="password123";          // Define Database Credentials here..(Must be same ones used in mysql server) , replace with your actual MySQL Server details. In this case, it's root and a random 4-digit number for the DB named as 'Test'.  
      Connection con = null;                       // Declare connection object to hold JDBC database connections... .    (Must be declared within try..catch block so we can close resources properly after operation).     If uncommented, add a MySQL server details.  In this case it's localhost at port number test for the db named as 'Test'.  
      Statement stmt = null;                      // Declare statement object to perform SQL operations... .    (Must be declared within try..catch block so we can close resources properly after operation).     If uncommented, add a MySQL server details.  In this case it's localhost at port number test for the db named as 'Test'.
