           stmt = con.createStatement();                   //Create a statement object... . (Must be declared within try block)   It is recommended to use these operations while working with Database or using any IO stream and close them after operation if not used here then it's mandatory for every Java program as start point ie.,main function..
           String sql = "SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE id="+1234;        //Define SQL Query... . (Must be declared within try block)   It is recommended to use these operations while working with Database or using any IO stream and close them after operation if not used here then it's mandatory for every Java program as start point ie.,main function..
           ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery(sql);                //Perform SQL Query... . (Must be declared within try block)   It is recommended to use these operations while working with Database or using any IO stream and close them after operation if not used here then it's mandatory for every Java program as start point ie.,main function..
           /*Process the ResultSet object */          //Uncomment this part, define how you want to process data. Un-Comment when done processing... .  If unprocessed, comment at end of code so that there is no leakage and it's mandatory for every Java program as start point ie.,main function..
